A4.text: The boroughs of New York City are the Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens, and Staten Island.

A5.text: Brooklyn is coextensive with Kings County.

A6.text: The modern city was formed by the 1898 consolidation of its five boroughs: Manhattan, Brooklyn, Queens, the Bronx, and Staten Island.

A7.text: New York City is sometimes referred to collectively as the Five Boroughs.

A8.text: Manhattan is the most densely populated and geographically smallest of the five boroughs of New York City.

A9.text: Coextensive with New York County, Manhattan is the smallest county by area in the U.S. state of New York.
